{{see|Wade}}
==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[wadan]], from common Germanic ''*wadan'', from Proto-Indo-European ''*wadh-'' "to go". Cognates include Latin [[vadere]] "go, walk; rush" (whence English [[invade]], [[evade]]).

